---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "Beautiful Mathematical Notation on the Web";
const description = "Implementing LaTeX-style mathematical equations in web content using KaTeX and modern markdown processors.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-8">
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <header class="mb-8">
      <div class="flex items-center text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">
        <time datetime="2025-08-22">August 22, 2025</time>
        <span class="mx-2">•</span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="mx-2">•</span>
        <span>by Mengkeat</span>
      </div>
      
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Beautiful Mathematical Notation on the Web</h1>
      
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Implementing LaTeX-style mathematical equations in web content using KaTeX and modern markdown processors.
      </p>
      
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
        <span class="inline-block bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-800 text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Math</span>
        <span class="inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-800 text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-full">LaTeX</span>
        <span class="inline-block bg-cyan-100 text-cyan-800 text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-full">KaTeX</span>
        <span class="inline-block bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-xs px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Web Dev</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <div class="max-w-none">
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Mathematical notation on the web has come a long way. With tools like KaTeX, we can now render beautiful, 
        LaTeX-style equations that are fast, accessible, and work across all modern browsers.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Why KaTeX?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        KaTeX is a fast, self-contained JavaScript library for rendering math notation. Unlike MathJax, 
        KaTeX renders equations synchronously and doesn't require a network connection for fonts.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Basic Examples</h2>
      
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Here's a simple inline equation: <span class="math inline">E = mc^2</span>
      </p>
      
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">And here's a block equation for the quadratic formula:</p>
      
      <div class="math display">x = \frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}</div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">More Complex Examples</h2>
      
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Matrix multiplication:</p>
      <div class="math display">
        \begin{bmatrix}
        a & b \\
        c & d
        \end{bmatrix}
        \begin{bmatrix}
        e & f \\
        g & h
        \end{bmatrix}
        =
        \begin{bmatrix}
        ae + bg & af + bh \\
        ce + dg & cf + dh
        \end{bmatrix}
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Calculus - the fundamental theorem:</p>
      <div class="math display">\int_a^b f'(x) \, dx = f(b) - f(a)</div>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Statistics - normal distribution:</p>
      <div class="math display">
        f(x) = \frac{1}{\sigma\sqrt{2\pi}} e^{-\frac{1}{2}\left(\frac{x-\mu}{\sigma}\right)^2}
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Implementation in Astro</h2>
      
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Setting up KaTeX in Astro is straightforward. You need to install the necessary packages 
        and configure your markdown processor to handle math notation.
      </p>

      <pre class="bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6 overflow-x-auto"><code class="text-sm">npm install remark-math rehype-katex katex</code></pre>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">Then configure your <code class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm">astro.config.mjs</code>:</p>

      <pre class="bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6 overflow-x-auto"><code class="text-sm">{`import { defineConfig } from 'astro/config';
import remarkMath from 'remark-math';
import rehypeKatex from 'rehype-katex';

export default defineConfig({
  markdown: {
    remarkPlugins: [remarkMath],
    rehypePlugins: [rehypeKatex],
  }
});`}</code></pre>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Best Practices</h2>
      
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-6 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Performance:</strong> KaTeX renders faster than MathJax</li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Includes proper ARIA labels</li>
        <li><strong>Fallbacks:</strong> Works without JavaScript enabled</li>
        <li><strong>Mobile:</strong> Equations scale well on small screens</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Advanced Features</h2>
      
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">KaTeX supports many advanced mathematical constructs:</p>
      
      <div class="math display">\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{1}{n^2} = \frac{\pi^2}{6}</div>

      <div class="math display">\lim_{x \to \infty} \left(1 + \frac{1}{x}\right)^x = e</div>

      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">And complex multi-line equations:</p>
      
      <div class="math display">
        \begin{align}
        \nabla \cdot \mathbf{E} &= \frac{\rho}{\epsilon_0} \\
        \nabla \cdot \mathbf{B} &= 0 \\
        \nabla \times \mathbf{E} &= -\frac{\partial \mathbf{B}}{\partial t} \\
        \nabla \times \mathbf{B} &= \mu_0\mathbf{J} + \mu_0\epsilon_0\frac{\partial \mathbf{E}}{\partial t}
        \end{align}
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
      
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        With KaTeX and modern web tools, we can create beautiful mathematical content that's 
        fast, accessible, and professional. Whether you're writing about machine learning, 
        physics, or pure mathematics, these tools make it easy to express complex ideas clearly.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Article Footer -->
    <footer class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-200">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
        <div class="flex items-center space-x-4">
          <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/40x40" alt="Mengkeat" class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full">
          <div>
            <div class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-900">Mengkeat</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Software Engineer & Blogger</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="flex space-x-4">
          <button class="text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-600 transition-colors">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path d="M15 8a3 3 0 10-2.977-2.63l-4.94 2.47a3 3 0 100 4.319l4.94 2.47a3 3 0 10.895-1.789l-4.94-2.47a3.027 3.027 0 000-.74l4.94-2.47C13.456 7.68 14.19 8 15 8z"></path>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <button class="text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-600 transition-colors">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M3.172 5.172a4 4 0 015.656 0L10 6.343l1.172-1.171a4 4 0 115.656 5.656L10 17.657l-6.828-6.829a4 4 0 010-5.656z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
            </svg>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </article>

  <!-- Related Posts -->
  <section class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Related Posts</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <article class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          <a href="/blog/jupyter-notebooks-web" class="hover:text-blue-600">Integrating Jupyter Notebooks</a>
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-3">
          Learn how to embed interactive notebooks in your web applications.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
          <span class="inline-block bg-orange-100 text-orange-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Jupyter</span>
          <span class="inline-block bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Python</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6 hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          <a href="/blog/marimo-reactive-notebooks" class="hover:text-blue-600">Reactive Notebooks with Marimo</a>
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mb-3">
          Discover the power of reactive programming in data science workflows.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1">
          <span class="inline-block bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Marimo</span>
          <span class="inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded-full">Notebooks</span>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .math.inline {
    display: inline;
  }
  
  .math.display {
    display: block;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
</style>
